[32m+[m[32m# Assertions[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Since most of the program already had custom assertions to check the preconditions and assure the correct behavior, we added only a few more to check the correctness of the program execution.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Methods that check the preconditions[m
[32m+[m[32m- Processor class - `check_register_index(index)`: Checks if the given index is a valid register index.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Processor class - `assert_16_bit(value)`: Truncates a value to fit within 16 bits.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Memory class - `check_instruction_memory_overflow(address)`: Checks for overflow in instruction memory.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Memory class - `check_instruction_memory_address(address)`: Checks if the address is within bounds of instruction memory.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Memory class - `check_data_memory_overflow(address)`: Checks for overflow in data memory.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Memory class - `check_memory_address(address)`: Checks if the address is within bounds of data memory.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Memory class - `validate_memory_size(size)`: Validates the memory size.[m
[32m+[m
